0:09:39.440 --> 0:09:42.520
So let me make him stop.

135
0:09:42.520 --> 0:09:44.360
All right.

136
0:09:44.360 --> 0:09:51.160
So the thumbs up gesture generally means okay, all good, let's proceed, something along that

137
0:09:51.160 --> 0:09:54.440
line, some sort of approval.

138
0:09:54.440 --> 0:10:00.040
However in some cultures that is a rude gesture.

139
0:10:00.040 --> 0:10:04.880
In ancient Rome it was contrary to popular belief the symbol that the gladiator should

140
0:10:04.880 --> 0:10:07.920
be put to death.

141
0:10:07.920 --> 0:10:19.200
In addition, in online forums, the definition has begun to modify and it is becoming, changing

142
0:10:19.200 --> 0:10:25.960
from approval to really a passive aggressive way to shut down a conversation.

143
0:10:25.960 --> 0:10:34.040
So all of this indicates that symbols, the meaning of symbols drifts over time and space.

144
0:10:34.040 --> 0:10:40.640
Now I moved from the US to Ireland a little over 10 years ago and discovered that there

145
0:10:40.640 --> 0:10:45.200
are two countries separated by a common language.

146
0:10:45.200 --> 0:10:51.640
For example, the phrase just about as in I just about caught the bus.

147
0:10:51.640 --> 0:10:57.080
Now in the US he would say I just about caught the bus, that means I ran after it and it

148
0:10:57.080 --> 0:10:58.400
left without me.

149
0:10:58.400 --> 0:11:00.520
I missed it.

150
0:11:00.520 --> 0:11:04.920
In Ireland, I just about caught the bus means I ran after it and I, my gosh, I managed to

151
0:11:04.920 --> 0:11:08.600
get on the thing and I got a lift.

152
0:11:08.600 --> 0:11:17.600
So they describe the same phrase both in English, both in a Western culture, describe two sides

153
0:11:17.600 --> 0:11:22.160
for opposite outcomes of the same event.

154
0:11:22.160 --> 0:11:27.320
So idioms are obviously another source of misunderstanding.

155
0:11:27.320 --> 0:11:33.680
So phrases like there's more than one way to skin a cat, which means there's more than

156
0:11:33.680 --> 0:11:41.880
one solution and is perfectly acceptable in a lot of cultures but there is obviously a

157
0:11:41.880 --> 0:11:43.240
chance of misunderstanding here.

158
0:11:43.240 --> 0:11:48.240
I actually had somebody ask me why would you skin a cat?

159
0:11:48.240 --> 0:11:56.800
Valid question but I don't know, that's just one of those things I learned in my culture.

160
0:11:56.800 --> 0:11:59.080
And then we'll get to the nodding head guy now.

161
0:11:59.080 --> 0:12:03.960
In general we think of that as the nodding head meaning yes.

162
0:12:03.960 --> 0:12:06.880
But in Bulgarian culture that means no.

163
0:12:06.880 --> 0:12:10.040
And in fact shaking your head from side to side means yes.

164
0:12:10.040 --> 0:12:12.840
Go figure.

165
0:12:12.840 --> 0:12:18.600
Now one more example here is that in some cultures it is acceptable and appropriate to

166
0:12:18.600 --> 0:12:24.160
