167
0:12:24.160 --> 0:12:27.720
So this indicates that you're listening, you're paying attention.

168
0:12:27.720 --> 0:12:33.520
Now in English you can see this when people say yes at the end of somebody's sentence

169
0:12:33.520 --> 0:12:35.960
all the time.

170
0:12:35.960 --> 0:12:40.760
The BBC television show Antiques Roadshow has examples of this all the time.

171
0:12:40.760 --> 0:12:45.320
This is a very valuable, yes, yes, they had known that at the beginning.

172
0:12:45.320 --> 0:12:47.640
Let's keep the conversation going.

173
0:12:47.640 --> 0:12:57.920
However in other cultures that's considered very rude to interrupt your speaker.

174
0:12:57.920 --> 0:13:00.480
My example three.

175
0:13:00.480 --> 0:13:05.960
There are words and phrases that are unacceptable in certain cultures.

176
0:13:05.960 --> 0:13:10.960
There are symbols and phrases that were I to use them here would probably get me reported

177
0:13:10.960 --> 0:13:16.800
for a violation of the code of conduct and derail this entire conversation.

178
0:13:16.800 --> 0:13:22.440
